title: 2013 - The Year In Christian Music (Bundle 45)
description:
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
2013 - THE YEAR IN CHRISTIAN MUSIC
-----------------------------------------------------------------------

More so than usual, if you like Rock, Hardcore, and/or Jazz then this is probably going to be the bundle for you.  There's a lot of Rock and Hardcore included within today's 45th bundle.  And never before have I included nearly this much Jazz in one bundle.  I probably only ever come across this much Jazz in an entire calendar year!  There are 9 Jazz albums here today, including two nice tributes to Faith Evans and Tamela Mann by the Smooth Jazz All Stars.

For anyone interested, my genre breakdown might look like this...

ROCK: 7eventh Time Down, Alter Bridge, Anberlin, Decyfer Down, Divided By Friday, Ed Kowalczyk, Everfound, Justin Jarvis, Scarlet Raven, Thousand Foot Krutch.  HIP-HOP/RAP: Akeemh, Anthony Valor, Croft, Fedel, Leo Powell, Phil Darko, Rhema Soul.  METAL/HARDCORE: August Burns Red, Being As An Ocean, Blessthefall, For All Eternity, I Am King, Impending Doom, Just Breathe, My Heart To Fear, Righteous Vendetta.  ELECTRONICA: Aurison.  JAZZ: Bart Brandjes, Dapaul, George Duke, Jacqui Dankworth, Nathaniel L Cole, Patrick Butler, Smooth Jazz All Stars, Tim Bowman.  CHRISTMAS: Brandon Heath, Chas Hathaway.  PRAISE & WORSHIP: Bryan And Katie Torwalt, Hymns Collective.  POP: Chris Cobbins, Josh Cogan.  ALTERNATIVE: The Current, Dimitris Rail, Icon For Hire, The Letter Black, Nine Lashes, Silversyde, Turnaround, We As Human.  CONTEMPORARY: Harvest Parker.  GOSPEL: Natasha Gray, Vadia

We have now shared 1,303 Christian Music titles this year.  That's only 158 titles (1461-1303), and 10 bundles (55 bundles-45 bundles) shy of last years totals.  Bundle 45 includes the following 54 releases...
